verses.text_plain: Then the Lord said unto Moses, Now shalt thou see what I will do to Pharaoh: for with a strong hand shall he let them go, and with a strong hand shall he drive them out of his land.
verses.verse_html: 1Then the Lord said unto Moses, Now shalt thou see what I will do to Pharaoh: for with a strong hand shall he let them go, and with a strong hand shall he drive them out of his land.

verses.text_plain: And God spake unto Moses, and said unto him, I am the Lord:
verses.verse_html:
2And God spake unto Moses, and said unto him, I am the Lord: ▼
▼ the Lord: or, Jehovah

verses.text_plain: And I appeared unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, by the name of God Almighty, but by my name Jehovah was I not known to them.
verses.verse_html: 3And I appeared unto Abraham, unto Isaac, and unto Jacob, by the name of God Almighty, but by my name Jehovah was I not known to them.

verses.text_plain: And I have also established my covenant with them, to give them the land of Canaan, the land of their pilgrimage, wherein they were strangers.
verses.verse_html: 4And I have also established my covenant with them, to give them the land of Canaan, the land of their pilgrimage, wherein they were strangers.

verses.text_plain: And I have also heard the groaning of the children of Israel, whom the Egyptians keep in bondage; and I have remembered my covenant.
verses.verse_html: 5And I have also heard the groaning of the children of Israel, whom the Egyptians keep in bondage; and I have remembered my covenant.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore say unto the children of Israel, I am the Lord, and I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will rid you out of their bondage, and I will redeem you with a stretched out arm, and with great judgments:
verses.verse_html: 6Wherefore say unto the children of Israel, I am the Lord, and I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will rid you out of their bondage, and I will redeem you with a stretched out arm, and with great judgments:

tokens.text: you out from under the burdens

verses.text_plain: And I will take you to me for a people, and I will be to you a God: and ye shall know that I am the Lord your God, which bringeth you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.
verses.verse_html: 7And I will take you to me for a people, and I will be to you a God: and ye shall know that I am the Lord your God, which bringeth you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.

tokens.text: you to me for a people
and I will be to you a God
you out from under the burdens

verses.text_plain: And I will bring you in unto the land, concerning the which I did swear to give it to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob; and I will give it you for an heritage: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
8And I will bring you in unto the land, concerning the which I did swear to give it to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob; and I will give it you for an heritage: I am the Lord. ▼
▼ swear: Heb. lift up my hand

tokens.text: concerning the which I did swear

footnotes.body_text: ▼ swear: Heb. lift up my hand
footnotes.body_html: ▼ swear: Heb. lift up my hand

verses.text_plain: And Moses spake so unto the children of Israel: but they hearkened not unto Moses for anguish of spirit, and for cruel bondage.
verses.verse_html:
9And Moses spake so unto the children of Israel: but they hearkened not unto Moses for anguish of spirit, and for cruel bondage. ▼
▼ anguish: Heb. shortness, or, straitness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ anguish: Heb. shortness, or, straitness

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 10And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Go in, speak unto Pharaoh king of Egypt, that he let the children of Israel go out of his land.
verses.verse_html: 11Go in, speak unto Pharaoh king of Egypt, that he let the children of Israel go out of his land.

verses.text_plain: And Moses spake before the Lord, saying, Behold, the children of Israel have not hearkened unto me; how then shall Pharaoh hear me, who am of uncircumcised lips?
verses.verse_html: 12And Moses spake before the Lord, saying, Behold, the children of Israel have not hearkened unto me; how then shall Pharaoh hear me, who am of uncircumcised lips?

tokens.text: unto me; how then shall Pharaoh

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, and gave them a charge unto the children of Israel, and unto Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt.
verses.verse_html: 13And the Lord spake unto Moses and unto Aaron, and gave them a charge unto the children of Israel, and unto Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt.

verses.text_plain: These be the heads of their fathers’ houses: The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel; Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi: these be the families of Reuben.
verses.verse_html: 14These be the heads of their fathers’ houses: The sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel; Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi: these be the families of Reuben.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Simeon; Jemuel, and Jamin, and Ohad, and Jachin, and Zohar, and Shaul the son of a Canaanitish woman: these are the families of Simeon.
verses.verse_html: 15And the sons of Simeon; Jemuel, and Jamin, and Ohad, and Jachin, and Zohar, and Shaul the son of a Canaanitish woman: these are the families of Simeon.

verses.text_plain: And these are the names of the sons of Levi according to their generations; Gershon, and Kohath, and Merari: and the years of the life of Levi were an hundred thirty and seven years.
verses.verse_html: 16And these are the names of the sons of Levi according to their generations; Gershon, and Kohath, and Merari: and the years of the life of Levi were an hundred thirty and seven years.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Gershon; Libni, and Shimi, according to their families.
verses.verse_html: 17The sons of Gershon; Libni, and Shimi, according to their families.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Kohath; Amram, and Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel: and the years of the life of Kohath were an hundred thirty and three years.
verses.verse_html: 18And the sons of Kohath; Amram, and Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel: and the years of the life of Kohath were an hundred thirty and three years.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Merari; Mahali and Mushi: these are the families of Levi according to their generations.
verses.verse_html: 19And the sons of Merari; Mahali and Mushi: these are the families of Levi according to their generations.

verses.text_plain: And Amram took him Jochebed his father’s sister to wife; and she bare him Aaron and Moses: and the years of the life of Amram were an hundred and thirty and seven years.
verses.verse_html: 20And Amram took him Jochebed his father’s sister to wife; and she bare him Aaron and Moses: and the years of the life of Amram were an hundred and thirty and seven years.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Izhar; Korah, and Nepheg, and Zichri.
verses.verse_html: 21And the sons of Izhar; Korah, and Nepheg, and Zichri.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Uzziel; Mishael, and Elzaphan, and Zithri.
verses.verse_html: 22And the sons of Uzziel; Mishael, and Elzaphan, and Zithri.

verses.text_plain: And Aaron took him Elisheba, daughter of Amminadab, sister of Naashon, to wife; and she bare him Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
verses.verse_html: 23And Aaron took him Elisheba, daughter of Amminadab, sister of Naashon, to wife; and she bare him Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Korah; Assir, and Elkanah, and Abiasaph: these are the families of the Korhites.
verses.verse_html: 24And the sons of Korah; Assir, and Elkanah, and Abiasaph: these are the families of the Korhites.

verses.text_plain: And Eleazar Aaron’s son took him one of the daughters of Putiel to wife; and she bare him Phinehas: these are the heads of the fathers of the Levites according to their families.
verses.verse_html: 25And Eleazar Aaron’s son took him one of the daughters of Putiel to wife; and she bare him Phinehas: these are the heads of the fathers of the Levites according to their families.

verses.text_plain: These are that Aaron and Moses, to whom the Lord said, Bring out the children of Israel from the land of Egypt according to their armies.
verses.verse_html: 26These are that Aaron and Moses, to whom the Lord said, Bring out the children of Israel from the land of Egypt according to their armies.

verses.text_plain: These are they which spake to Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring out the children of Israel from Egypt: these are that Moses and Aaron.
verses.verse_html: 27These are they which spake to Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring out the children of Israel from Egypt: these are that Moses and Aaron.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass on the day when the Lord spake unto Moses in the land of Egypt,
verses.verse_html: 28And it came to pass on the day when the Lord spake unto Moses in the land of Egypt,

tokens.text: And it came to pass on the day

verses.text_plain: That the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, I am the Lord: speak thou unto Pharaoh king of Egypt all that I say unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 29That the Lord spake unto Moses, saying, I am the Lord: speak thou unto Pharaoh king of Egypt all that I say unto thee.

verses.text_plain: And Moses said before the Lord, Behold, I am of uncircumcised lips, and how shall Pharaoh hearken unto me?
verses.verse_html: 30And Moses said before the Lord, Behold, I am of uncircumcised lips, and how shall Pharaoh hearken unto me?
